We only look at the “Initial” transactions. In this problem the first three rows are initial transactions in which the company records its paid‐in capital. They are:

• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 5,000,000.0

Adding these numbers gives 3,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 = 13,000,000.0, which is both the opening (initial) paid‐in capital and, with no additional paid‐in capital transactions later, the ending paid‐in capital remains the same.

Thus the final answer is:

{"solution": {'Paid-in Capital Initial Value': '13000000.00', 'Paid-in Capital End Value': '13000000.00'}}
